Public Lending Reward.
The way the lending platform works tries to ensure fair system for all NFT staking to be rewarded regardless of how "lucky" they were with who borrowed their character.
The pool for all staked NFTs is the total rewards generated by all players who borrowed a character, with a minimum guarantee that is determined by the amount of NFTs staked.
The pool is distributed every Wed at 12pm among all staked NFTs (ie, on a weekly basis) where each NFT is getting their part of the pool which is based on 3 factors:
1. Time in the lending platform (how much time of the week the NFT was staked)
2. The rarity of the NFT
3. The level of the NFT

At your Verko wallet (
), you can see the total pool prize which is updated every 10 minutes, number of NFTs staked, and your lended NFTs with estimated earning for each.
